Netas Telekommunikasyon AS (NETAS) , a maker of
telecommunications equipment, fell after reporting a loss in the
first quarter from a profit a year earlier.  The shares dropped 3.9 percent to 235.50 liras at the close
in Istanbul, taking their weekly slide to 4.3 percent. The stock
is up 92 percent this year, compared with a 15 percent rise in
 Turkey â€™s ISE National 100 Index.  Netas swung to a 34.5 million-lira ($19.6 million) loss,
compared with a 3.2 million-lira profit a year ago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
